ECB’s Weidmann Says Larger Bailout Amounts Don’t Solve Crisis

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s   a n d   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-10-14T17:09:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/ecb-s-weidmann-says-larger-bailout-amounts-don-t-solve-crisis.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Jens Weidmann said that  Europe  shouldn’t keep
devoting larger amounts of money to trying to solve the debt
crisis.  “Reacting with ever-greater means is surely not helpful,”
Weidmann said in an interview with  Germany ’s ZDF television
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
